subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnostic features:
Face flat, with indistinct facial tubercle (
Fig. 5
), and with pale and slightly developed facial stripe (
Fig. 8
). Flagellomere short, less than three times as long as pedicel (
Fig. 13
). Spurious vein ending before meeting point of vein M with discal cross-vein (as in 
Fig. 21
). Male genitalia: epandrium in narrower part less than half the length of the cercus (
Figs 40, 42
) or as long as cercus (
Fig. 38
); ejaculatory apodema small, apical part simple, two- dimensional (
Figs 101–103
); lateral lobe of aedeagus anteriorly protruded as much as or more than postgonites (
Figs 55–57
); aedeagal apodeme without welldeveloped lateral arms (
Figs 79, 81
), but with strong beak-like dorsal prolongation (
Figs 66, 67
, 
78, 80
).
